servational evidence of particle filtration by gap-opening\nplanets. The observed sub-millimeter continuum emission at the vicinity of the\nplanets can be reproduced when (sub-)$\\mu$m grains survive over multiple\ncircumplanetary disk gas viscous timescales and accumulate therein. One such\npossibility is if (sub-)$\\mu$m grains grow in size and remain trapped in\npressure bumps, similar to what we find happening in circumstellar disks. We\ndiscuss potential implications to planet formation in the solar system and\nmature extrasolar planetary systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Sep 2019 13:00:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-06"}
