 dominant multipole contribution, the\ndipole, at sufficient large distances, it is shown that, for two interacting\nemitters, as their separation distance increases, the fractional change in apex\nFEF, $\\delta$, decreases following a power law with exponent $-3$. The result\nis extended for conducting emitters having an arbitrary axially-symmetric\nshape, where it is also shown $\\delta$ has a pre-factor depending on geometry,\nconfirming the tendency observed in recent analytical and numerical results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Sep 2019 15:17:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-24"}
